Dear Shin,
 
RYDE CITY COUNCIL has asked for additional information as part of your application for development PAN-132220  at L4 33 ROWE STREET EASTWOOD 2122.

The request is: Hi Shin

Reference is made to your application for 33-35 Rowe Street, Eastwood – for conversion of 4th floor into offices (LDA 2021/294). Please be advised that Council’s Building Surveyor has reviewed the proposal and has advised:

BCA Report: A review of the architectural plans revealed that the BCA Classification has changed from the Class 3 to a Class 5, therefore, a comprehensive BCA Compliance Report is required to ensure compliance with the relevant provisions of the BCA. It will be necessary to submit a BCA Compliance Report (instead of a “BCA Capability Statement”) to demonstrate how the proposed office fitout when completed will be able to achieve compliance or meet the performance requirements of National Construction Code Building Code of Australia Volume One 2019 Amendment 1. The report must be signed and dated by the suitably qualified consultant.

A review of the BCA capability statement revealed that under most provisions of the BCA “Compliance is Readily Achievable” (CBA), however not enough information has not been provided to demonstrate compliance with the relevant provisions of the BCA from suitably qualified consultants.
• Please note that the Structural design, existing fire services, mechanical, electrical, hydraulic design will be affected as a result of the proposed fitout. Please provide existing as well as proposed fire services, mechanical, electrical, and hydraulic services design documentation in support of the BCA Report for further review.
• Please also provide the structural design and adequacy certificate for the proposed fitout in support of the BCA Report.
• An existing and proposed fire safety schedule will also be required.

Please submit the above information within 14 days from the date of this email.

Sandra McCarry
Senior Town Planner
DEVELOPMENT ASSESSMENT.
